## Acceptance Criteria

1. A `tool_progress` SDK message with `{ type: 'tool_progress', tool_use_id: 'tc-1', content: 'output' }` yields exactly one `StreamEvent` with `{ type: 'tool_progress', data: { toolCallId: 'tc-1', content: 'output' } }`
2. The handler returns early (does not fall through to other handlers)
3. The test file passes: `pnpm vitest run apps/server/src/services/core/__tests__/sdk-event-mapper.test.ts`
4. All existing tests in the file continue to pass
5. No changes to existing handler logic — this is purely additive

Add `tool_progress` event handling to the client-side stream event handler and add the `progressOutput` field to the `ToolCallState` type.

## Files to Modify

### 1. `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/chat-types.ts`

Add `progressOutput` to the `ToolCallState` interface (line 22-34). Insert after `result?: string;` (line 26):

```typescript
export interface ToolCallState {
  toolCallId: string;
  toolName: string;
  input: string;
  result?: string;
  /** Intermediate output from tool_progress events (cleared when result arrives) */
  progressOutput?: string;
  status: 'pending' | 'running' | 'complete' | 'error';
  /** Set when this tool call requires interactive UI (approval or question) */
  interactiveType?: 'approval' | 'question';
  /** Question data when interactiveType is 'question' */
  questions?: QuestionItem[];
  /** Submitted answers (present when restored from history) */
  answers?: Record<string, string>;
}
```

### 2. `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/stream-event-handler.ts`

**2a. Add `ToolProgressEvent` to the import (line 1-14)**

Add `ToolProgressEvent` to the import from `@dorkos/shared/types`:

